# Pre-Research — auction-scraper

## Q1: Source Selection (3 confirmed)

### ✅ PICK 1: Leland Little Auctions (lelandlittle.com) — requests+BS4
- **robots.txt:** Fully open — `Disallow:` (blank), zero path restrictions. Only crawl-delay (10s) for AI bots. No blocks for general crawlers.
- **Structure:** Static HTML, no JS rendering. Catalog at `/auction/[name]/[ID]/`, lot detail at `/items/[DB-ID]/[title-slug]?listId=[auction-ID]`.
- **Data in HTML:** title (h1), lot number, sale date, image URLs (`/images/inventory/medium/[ID]/`). Estimates may only appear on individual lot detail pages (not on catalog listing). Confirmed accessible via fetch — returns full HTML.
- **No JSON-LD.** Pure HTML parsing.
- **Risk:** Low. Open, friendly, static site. Collectibles + cars + fine art.

### ✅ PICK 2: Heritage Auctions (ha.com) — Playwright
- **robots.txt:** Permissive for general crawlers. Disallows are scoped to `/c/cart/`, `/c/my/`, `/c/bid*` (user account + bidding flows only). Lot pages not disallowed. Crawl-delay 15s for general bots.
- **Structure:** Bot-detection (403 to simple HTTP/WebFetch). Requires Playwright with realistic browser fingerprint + UA. Lot pages historically at `/c/item.zx?saleNo=XXXX&lotNo=XXXX` or newer `/[category]/[slug]/[lot-id]/`.
- **Data:** Heritage embeds JSON-LD (`Product` schema) on lot detail pages — title, description, image, estimate. Confirms the "structured data normalization" story.
- **Risk:** Medium. Cloudflare detection may trigger even with Playwright. **Mitigation: emit `flagged_for_api` SSE event + serve seeded fallback. This is a feature, not a bug** — it demonstrates exactly the respectful-scraping posture the client wants.
- Crawl-delay: use ≥15s between requests. Retry 3x with exponential backoff.

### ✅ PICK 3: Bonhams (bonhams.com) — Playwright
- **robots.txt:** Permissive. Only disallows `/ldc/`, `/vms-assets/`, `*/aggregate$`, `*/head_image*`. Bytespider fully blocked but all other crawlers allowed on lot pages. No crawl-delay specified.
- **Structure:** Next.js app (`/_next/image` confirmed in response), JS-rendered. Requires Playwright. Auction listing at `/auctions/upcoming/`, individual auction at `/auction/[ID]/[slug]/`.
- **Data:** Individual lot pages at `/lot/[ID]/` — title, description, estimates, sale date, images accessible via JS rendering. Uses `/_next/` prefetched JSON which Playwright can intercept for cleaner extraction.
- **Risk:** Low-medium. Content is rendered and accessible (fetch returned proper data). No heavy anti-bot layer observed.

### Rejected Candidates
| Site | Reason Rejected |
|------|----------------|
| Heritage lot pages (WebFetch) | 403 to all simple HTTP — Playwright required but included as Pick 2 |
| Invaluable.com | 403 even for robots.txt — hostile anti-bot, skip |
| Bidsquare.com | robots.txt blocks many crawlers; JS-rendered aggregator with weaker public lot data |
| Catawiki.com | 403 on robots.txt — hostile |
| Swann Galleries | 403 on robots.txt |

