## Q2: Structure Per Selected Source

### Leland Little
```
Catalog URL: /auction/{name}/{auction-id}/
Lot URL:     /items/{item-db-id}/{title-slug}?listId={auction-id}
Pagination:  URL-based (?page=N) or all lots on one page (small auctions)

Fields:
  title       → h1 text
  lot_number  → text before "·" in listing cards / breadcrumb
  images      → img[src] under /images/inventory/medium/{id}/
  sale_date   → header text in catalog page ("Jun 24, 2026, 12:00pm")
  description → body text on lot detail page
  estimate    → likely in lot detail page body text (needs individual page fetch)
  currency    → USD (assumed, domestic auctions)
```
**Approach:** `requests` + `BeautifulSoup`. One GET for catalog (paginated if needed), one GET per lot for description + estimate. 2s delay between requests.

### Heritage Auctions
```
Catalog URL: /c/search-results.zx?type=191&N={category-codes}
Lot URL:     /c/item.zx?saleNo={sale}&lotNo={lot} (legacy)
             /{category}/{title}/{lot-id}m.s (newer clean URLs)
Pagination:  URL param &p=N or next-page link

Fields (via JSON-LD Product schema on lot page):
  title       → JSON-LD "name"
  description → JSON-LD "description"
  images      → JSON-LD "image" array
  estimate    → JSON-LD "offers.price" or text in .lot-estimate span
  sale_date   → JSON-LD "event.startDate" or text in .sale-date
  lot_number  → URL param or .lot-number span
```
**Approach:** Playwright headless + intercept JSON-LD. 15s+ between requests. If 403/Cloudflare → emit `flagged_for_api`, return seeded Heritage lots.

### Bonhams
```
Catalog URL: /auction/{id}/{slug}/
Lot URL:     /lot/{lot-id}/
Pagination:  /auction/{id}/{slug}/?page=N

Fields (JS-rendered, Playwright):
  title       → h1.lot-title
  description → .lot-description div
  images      → img in .lot-images gallery / /_next prefetch JSON
  estimate    → .lot-estimate text (e.g. "£3,000 – 5,000")
  sale_date   → .auction-date text
  lot_number  → .lot-number or breadcrumb
```
**Approach:** Playwright, wait for `.lot-title` to appear. Intercept `/_next/data/*.json` if available for cleaner extraction. 3s between lots.

